Name: hintText

Type: property

Syntax: set the hintText of field to <hintString>

Summary:
Specifies placeholder text displayed inside a field when it is empty.

Associations: field

Introduced: 1.0.0

OS: mac, windows, linux

Platforms: desktop, server

Example:
set the hintText of field "Search" to "Type to search..."

Example:
set the hintText of field "Email" to "name@example.com"

Example:
set the hintText of field "Username" to empty -- remove hint text

Value:
The <hintText> of a <field> is a <string>. By default, the <hintText>
of a newly created <field> is empty.

Description:
Use the <hintText> property to display a short prompt or example value
inside a field when the field contains no text. This is commonly used
to label an input field without requiring a separate label object, or
to show the expected format of an entry such as a date or email address.

The hint text is drawn in a grey colour and disappears as soon as the
field contains any content. It is for display only and is never included
in the field's <text> property or any other text-retrieving expression.

Setting the <hintText> property to empty removes the hint.

>*Note:* The <hintText> property is distinct from the field's <label>
> property. The <label> is shown outside the field as its visible name,
> while <hintText> is shown inside the field and is only visible when the
> field is empty.

References: text (property), label (property), field (object),
string (keyword)

Tags: ui

